     dlsch_ue_select[CC_idP].list[dlsch_ue_select[CC_idP].ue_num].UE_id = UE_id;
     dlsch_ue_select[CC_idP].list[dlsch_ue_select[CC_idP].ue_num].rnti = rnti;
     dlsch_ue_select[CC_idP].ue_num++;
   }
   ```

3. This function is called from `eNB_scheduler_RA.c` when scheduling Msg4 for random access procedures.

4. The problem is that there's no bounds checking in `set_dl_ue_select_msg4()`. If `ue_num` is already 20 when this function is called, it will write to `list[20]`, which is out of bounds (valid indices are 0-19).

5. Similarly, `set_dl_ue_select_msg2()` has the same issue.

The fix is to add bounds checking in both `set_dl_ue_select_msg2()` and `set_dl_ue_select_msg4()` functions to ensure `ue_num` doesn't exceed the array size (20).


